<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Luang Prabang</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[UNESCO old town at the confluence of the Mekong and Nam Khan. Climb Mount Phousi for sunset over the Mekong. Wat Xieng Thong (1559) is the masterpiece of Lao temple architecture. Morning alms-round at dawn (be respectful — observe quietly, don't crowd the monks).]]></description><Point><coordinates>102.135600,19.885600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Kuang Si Falls (spur from Luang Prabang)</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[30 km southwest. Multi-tier limestone falls cascading into turquoise pools you can swim in. Black bear sanctuary at the entrance (rescued from bile farms).]]></description><Point><coordinates>102.085000,19.865000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Phou Khoun</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Hill-junction village at 1,250 m — last stop on the Plain of Jars detour east. The Plain (a 90 km detour) holds thousands of Iron Age stone jars whose purpose is still debated.]]></description><Point><coordinates>102.540000,19.451700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Vang Vieng</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Karst peaks rising from rice paddies above the Nam Song. Hot-air balloon flights at sunrise (book ahead). Blue Lagoon swimming holes (multiple, all called Blue Lagoon — go to #2 or #3 to escape the crowds at #1). Caves: Tham Phu Kham.]]></description><Point><coordinates>102.447500,18.924400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Vientiane</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[That Luang (1566) is the national stupa — gold, three-tiered, the symbol on Lao currency. Patuxai is a 1960s Lao take on the Arc de Triomphe ('the vertical runway' — built with US aid concrete intended for an airport). Mekong sunset from the riverbank esplanade.]]></description><Point><coordinates>102.633100,17.975700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
